#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:2
msgid "Aligner"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:4
msgid ""
"Alignment involves creating a bilingual translation memory from "
"monolingual documents that have already been translated."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:7
msgid "To access this window, select Tools > Align Files...."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:10
msgid "Step 1: Adjust the alignment parameters"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:12
msgid ""
"If the alignment looks as if it could be improved, try changing the "
"parameters. In most cases, the lower the Average score is, better the "
"alignment will be."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:16
msgid ""
"In Heapwise mode, the texts are evaluated globally. In Parsewise mode, "
"they are evaluated segment by segment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:19
msgid ""
"Use ID comparison mode to align Key=Value texts. This works even if the "
"keys are not in the same order in the two files, and/or if the two files "
"do not contain the same amount of information. This option only appears "
"if both the selected files are recognised as Key=Value files."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:24
msgid ""
"The Viterbi and Forward-Backward algorithms are two different calculation"
" methods. Choose the one that provides the best results."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:27
msgid "Click Continue to access the next step."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:30
msgid "Step 2: Make manual corrections"
msgstr "Ã‰tape 2 : apporter des corrections manuelles"

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:32
msgid ""
"After the automatic process, the alignment of two files generally "
"requires manual corrections."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:35
msgid "Translation units are located in cells in the two last columns."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:37
msgid "To align two segments on the same line:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:39
msgid "Select the first segment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:41
msgid "Press the space bar (shortcut for Edit > Start Pinpoint Align)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:43
msgid ""
"Click in the other column on the translation corresponding to the first "
"segment."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:46
msgid ""
"After several of these operations, select Edit > Realign pending to "
"update the alignment of the other segments."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:49
msgid ""
"To modify the position of one or more segments individually, select the "
"segment(s) and press ``U`` (Move Up) or ``D`` (Move Down)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:52
msgid ""
"Only rows with the Keep box ticked in the first column will be included "
"when the translation memory is created."
msgstr ""

#: ../../source/Windows_Aligner.rst:55
msgid ""
"When the two columns are sufficiently aligned, click Save TMX... to "
"create the resulting translation memory."
msgstr ""

